 News Analysis: Following President Muhammadu Buhari’s intervention, Politicians have begun to plot fresh moves ahead of 2023 general election. just as reports revealed that some founders and pillars of the All Progressive Congress, have returned to the drawing board digging in for 2023 polls.   Vanguard Following President Muhammadu Buhari’s intervention, some founders and pillars of the All Progressives Congress, APC, have returned to the trenches to restrategise and plot fresh plans to realise their 2023 political quests. July 1, 2020 In "News" Early campaign or what some political analysts would rightly call ‘jumping the gun’ is part of what blights our electoral process. August 11, 2019 In "Viewpoint" The sack of close associates of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu in the just dissolved National Working Committee, NWC of the All Progressives Congress, APC is the first step towards redesigning political interests ahead of President Muhammadu Buhari’s exit in 2023, Saturday Vanguard has learnt. June 27, 2020 In "News"